Policy.acknowledgement_statement: "This study is part of the NHLBI Grand Opportunity Exome Sequencing Project (GO-ESP). Funding for GO-ESP was provided by NHLBI grants RC2 HL103010 (HeartGO), RC2 HL102923 (LungGO) and RC2 HL102924 (WHISP). The exome sequencing was performed through NHLBI grants RC2 HL102925 (BroadGO) and RC2 HL102926 (SeattleGO). Collection of the cystic fibrosis data and specimens was supported by Awards GIBSON07K0, KNOWLE00A0, OBSERV04K0, and RDP R026 from the Cystic Fibrosis Foundation; NHLBI grants R01 HL068890 and R01 HL095396; NCRR grant UL1RR025014 and NHGRI grant R00 HG004316."
Policy.ic_specific_access_term: There are two consent groups for use of these data: 1) the use of the data from the consent group of University of Washington is limited to genetic research that facilitates discovery of variation related to cystic fibrosis (CF), and 2) the use of the data from the consent group of Universities of North Carolina is limited to the general research use (GRU).
